column3: â€œtwo of my absolute favorite strains, Haze and Train Wreck, come together to create  a near perfect experience. it gave me total focus. i felt totally free to think outside the box and be creative. i was motivated to be productive. i also felt this really familiar sense of well being similar to some of my best childhood memories. toward the end i laughed harder than i have in a while. made me talkative too but on a ph...â€

â€œHaze Wreck is one of few strains that I've tried with distinctly energizing effects. A great strain for when you're pulling late nights and don't want to feel sedated. The buzz leaves you pretty functional and focused -- great for creative activities. It also has a really nice mango aroma and taste! Haze Wreck is my new favorite. I'll be very sad when I reach the end of this jar.â€
â€œthis one was uplifting. good for getting the day going. good for keeping it going when you are getting tired. short list this oneâ€
â€œOne of the best strains I have ever had. It made my clean my apartment. Gives you great energy. Great high. I highly recommend this strain. I'm glad they finally have it on leafly.â€

â€œSmooth smoke that tastes like dog shit and mint. Focused and energetic. Puts up the blinders so you can gitrdone. 3 stars only due to taste and the seriousness. Did not get the euphoric well being typical of more citrusy strains. Version was Hazy Train from Farma.â€
â€œOne of my faves! Motivated in a relaxed way, not manic. You'll get 'er done - it may not be at your fastest pace, but it'll be pleasant. Made me feel very content.â€

â€œJust got this stuff the other day and its great. It is a really sweet skunky cheese scent & taste. The high is a strong head high with a good amount of haziness. half a bowl of this stuff and im annihilated.â€

â€œone of my all time favorites. It's great for destressing with a perfect sativa high that you can get lost in and not mind. I thought it's a great social strain, but not good to stay on task with.â€
